:\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Docker setup for tests**\\n\\nIf the generated tests require actual driver behavior, I might need to use a Docker Neo4j image along with credentials. The setup could involve figuring out which image or tag to use, like Neo4j 5.28. I’m thinking the official image, such as `neo4j:5.28.8`, could be the way to go. However, I should also check other tags like `neo4j:5.26-community` or `neo4j:5.28-community` to ensure I'm choosing the safest and most appropriate option for the tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ER4pknGYA0cgP5AJQOM4lrgg|fc_0a5362e8992472f7016a425eef482881969d5ad33b8f9091fa", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -name build.gradle -print | xargs rg -n \"docker|testcontainers|allowed|Testcontainers|jdbc|postgres|neo4j\" -S | head -100; find . -maxdepth 3 -iname '*docker*' -o -iname '*allowed*' | head -50", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 905, "output": 636, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34821, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782734562905, "responseId": "resp_0a5362e8992472f7016a425ee37a2c8196a9be668772560909"}}
